• Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. JOHANNESBURG - Convicted racist Vicki Momberg's application for leave to appeal her sentence has been postponed to 18 April. This is for the defense to submit supplementary papers. #VickiMomberg on the dock. Matter postponed to 18 April for defense to submit supplementary papers pic.twitter.com/QFQRnzJTT5 She appeared in the Randburg magistrate’s court on Wednesday. Last month, Momberg was sentenced to three years in prison, with one year suspended. She was found guilty on four counts of crimen injuria for hurling racial slurs at black officials who tried to help her after a smash-and-grab incident. UPDATE: Vicki Momberg's appeal application postponed Her tirade was caught on camera. She was denied bail pending her appeal. Magistrate Pravina Raghoonandan found Momberg had shown no remorse for her actions. eNCA